GeneralDesc: Adirondack - Inverter 3.10 - Forced Outage. 7/3/19 10:00 Adirondack Inverter 3.10 stopped producing. C4 has no remote access to this site. (not in LastPass). See Screen Shot.. 010 - Over temperature
CompletionDesc: 7/18/2019 Tim Chaput - Verified tripped AC breaker upon arrival at the site. - Took inverters 3-9 & 3-11 off line (AC & DC) - Opened panelboard 3 main breaker in switchboard, and LOTO'ed. - Removed both covers from inverter 3-10 & panelboard 3 including dead front. - Verified no power (live-dead-live). - Found no issues internal to inverter 3-10 (same as last inspection). - Replaced defective 100A, 3 pole, Eaton breaker with new. Noted heat damage to B phase of old breaker (see photos). - Replaced all covers. - Closed all breakers, and checked voltage (all good). - Placed all 3 inverters back into service with no issues. All 3 returned to service. - Using front display, and noted all AC voltages, on all 3 inverters good, and well within spec. - Will monitor this inverter in the coming days.

GeneralDesc: WO-00007208 ; IS 46 ; Central Inverter - Production Outage ;. Inverter E-A7-2 offline. Modules damaged causing ground fault. CB to be isolated.---Created By; Julien Glover on: 10/26/2017. 001 - Ground fault
CompletionDesc: 26 Oct: We were alerted to an inverter outage at E-A7-2 at 1045. Upon investigation, we discovered that a skid-steer operator from HBC (working on the site roads per Punchlist) hit two modules. This caused a Ground Fault in the array and tripped the inverter offline. Pictures Attached. Work Performed: We alerted Entropy (as they are the responsible contractor) and HBC. The supervisors for both came to the location. In an effort to get the inverter back online asap, CCR took lead. CCR Opened and LOTO'd the applicable CB. We then cleared and reset the inverter. It came back online with no issues. It was producing again by 1130. At that time, Entropy was cleared to replace the broken modules. CCR ensured the Source-Circuits were unplugged before work began. Entropy workers had the modules replaced within 30 minutes. CCR then inspected the work, connected the Source Circuit wiring to the String Wiring and took voltage measurements to ensure proper Voc. The fuses in the CB were tested and tested OK. All string touch-safe fuse holders were closed in with the exception of the string that was just addressed with the repair. The CB was then CLOSED in and voltage/current measurements were taken to ensure there were no issues. Lastly, the repaired string was closed in and held with no issues. The area was cleaned and cleared with no issues and all repairs were successful.. TechDispatched: No

GeneralDesc: Highway 56 - inverter 2.1 - not communicating. Highway 56 - inverter 2.1 - not communicating - after scheduled outage 5-Apr the site was brought back online - inverter 2.1 is not communicating but using meter data it appears all inverters are producing at this time. When technician arrived on site inverter 2.1 was operating but not communicating. Technician isolated inverter and then tested and verified communication cable was not damaged Technician then restarted the inverter and once the inverter was brought back online communications had been reestablished. Technician called and verified that C4 was able to see the inverter again. -SMA informed us during the last site visit that a hard reset of the inverter usually resolves communication issues. Update (04/18/19): Inverter failed to communicate or start up with the rest of the inverters and likely needs another hard reset. 020 - Data/Communication System Outage

GeneralDesc: WO-00005725 ; IS 46 ; Central Inverter - Communications Outage ;. Inverter E-B5-1 has intermittent communications.---Created By; Joseph Sheffield on: 08/17/2017. 020 - Data/Communication System Outage
CompletionDesc: 14 August: E-B5-1 is the new inverter that was commissioned last week. It has had intermittent comms since Monday (14 Aug). It would go down and then come back up. I called Martin (Kaco tech) on Monday and he said to monitor it. The issue continued until today. 17 August: Today (17 Aug) the comms never came online this morning. We went back to the field and tried to reset the inverter at the HMI and this was not successful. I called Martin again and he walked us through the process of reloading the HMI software using an SD card from the neighboring inverter. We followed his steps exactly but this did not bring the inverter back online. Martin is scheduled to come out tomorrow and he will be bringing an new HMI. 23 August: Kaco has been working on site since Monday (21 August) performing the PRC-024 inverter software updates. I had them evaluate E-B5-1 again. As we monitored E-B5 throughout the day, we noticed that when it was communicating E-B7 was not, and when E-B7 was communicating E-B5 was not. Once we explained that to the Kaco technician, they went back to E-B5 and reprogrammed the HMI. The issue was that E-B5 and E-B7 had the same addresses. That has been fixed now and both E-B7 and E-B5 are communicating normally now.. TechDispatched: No

GeneralDesc: WO-00005976 ; IS 46 ; Central Inverter - Production Outage ;. Inverter E-A7-1 has faulted offline.---Created By; Joseph Sheffield on: 09/05/2017. 019 - Unplanned outage/derate
CompletionDesc: Sept 5: Technician went to inverter to investigate it being online but showing 0 kW production. The inverter was found to be in fault and was not producing. The following steps were utilized to successfully clear the fault: 1) The DC disconnects were placed in the OPEN position. 2) The inverter was keyed to the OFF position. 3) Circuit Breaker 21 was placed in the OPEN position. 4) Technicians opened the HMI cabinet and visually inspected the various breakers inside the cabinet. Two were found to be in the OPEN position. Technician cycled them and placed them in the CLOSED position. 4) GFI breaker was visually checked and found to be in the CLOSED position. 5) The inverter was closed back up and restarted according to the manufacturer's instructions. 6) The inverter came back online and began production after the mandatory AC sync period.. TechDispatched: No
